@ecojydrology @nceas and cannot fund international travel. But we would welcome any advice you might have to better share this information with northern communities - as it is something we are working to continually improve!

@ecojydrology @nceas We're working to increase our outreach and engagement with the Arctic community so that everyone who is interested in participating is aware of these opportunities. We will be holding similar workshops in the future, but do have some funding restrictions on the location

@ecojydrology @nceas @ecojydrology this workshop was indeed in a warm place, but the diverse group came from across the Arctic & Arctic research field. Costs were covered for all participants (flights, hotels, meals), and the workshop was open to all Arctic researchers & community members
